This article is a Presidential Proclamation issued by Barack Obama on September 4, 2009, in honor of Labor Day. The proclamation recognizes the contributions of working Americans throughout the history of the United States and acknowledges their role in building the nation's infrastructure, manufacturing goods, providing services, and caring for others. It highlights the labor movement's advocacy for decent working conditions, fair wages, and benefits, and emphasizes the challenges faced by the country during an economic crisis. The proclamation calls upon public officials and all citizens to observe Labor Day with appropriate programs and activities that recognize the contributions of working Americans and their families.